\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
y^{(n+1)}=Ay^{(n)}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $y^{(n)}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y^{(n+1)}$
\end_inset

 are the values of 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 predicted by the numerical method at time-steps 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $n+1$
\end_inset

.
